{"doc":{"isMarkdown":false,"isTranslated":true,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"Canvas","mdn_url":"/es/docs/Glossary/Canvas","locale":"es","native":"Español","sidebarHTML":"","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p><span class=\"seoSummary\">El <strong>elemento canvas</strong> forma parte de <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HTML5\" title=\"HTML5\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">HTML5</a> y habilita dinamismo,<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scripting_language\" title=\"Scripting language\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\"> de scripts</a> <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rendering_(computer_graphics)\" title=\"Rendering (computer graphics)\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">lenguaje</a> de figuras en 2D &amp; 3 3D e imágenes de<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bitmap\" title=\"Bitmap\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\"> mapas de Bits</a> images.</span> esta en un bajo nivel, el modelo de procedimiento actualiza el<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bitmap\" title=\"Bitmap\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\"> mapa de bits</a> y no tiene que construir en él<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scene_graph\" title=\"un gráfico de escena\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\"> scene graph</a>. Ofrece una zona gráfica vacía en la cual especifica <a href=\"/es/docs/Glossary/JavaScript\">JavaScript</a> <a href=\"/es/docs/Glossary/API\">APIs</a> puede dibujar (como en Canvas 2D o <a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Glossary/WebGL\">WebGL <small>(en-US)</small></a>).</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"aprende_más","title":"Aprende más","isH3":false,"content":""}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"conocimientos_básicos","title":"Conocimientos básicos","isH3":true,"content":"<ul>\n <li><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Canvas_(HTML)\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">Canvas en Wikipedia</a></li>\n</ul>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"inicio_del_temario","title":"Inicio del temario","isH3":true,"content":"<ul>\n <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Guide/HTML/Canvas_tutorial\">Tutorial de Canvas en MDN</a></li>\n</ul>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"información_técnica","title":"Información técnica","isH3":true,"content":"<ul>\n <li>The HTML <a href=\"/es/docs/Web/HTML/Element/canvas\"><code>&lt;canvas&gt;</code></a> element on MDN</li>\n <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/HTML/Canvas\">Documentación general de Canvas en MDN</a></li>\n <li><a href=\"/es/docs/Web/API/CanvasRenderingContext2D\"><code>CanvasRenderingContext2D</code></a>: API de Canvas2D dibujando</li>\n <li><a href=\"https://www.w3.org/TR/2dcontext/\" rel=\"external noopener\" class=\"external\">Canvas 2D, especificaciones del API</a></li>\n</ul>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Aprende más","id":"aprende_más"}],"summary":"El elemento canvas forma parte de HTML5 y habilita dinamismo, de scripts lenguaje de figuras en 2D & 3 3D e imágenes de mapas de Bits images.","popularity":0,"modified":"2022-07-19T02:29:32.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"Canvas","locale":"de","native":"Deutsch"},{"title":"Canvas","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)"},{"title":"Canvas","locale":"fr","native":"Français"},{"title":"Canvas","locale":"ja","native":"日本語"},{"title":"Canvas","locale":"ru","native":"Русский"},{"title":"Canvas","locale":"zh-CN","native":"中文 (简体)"},{"title":"Canvas","locale":"zh-TW","native":"正體中文 (繁體)"}],"source":{"folder":"es/glossary/canvas","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/translated-content/blob/main/files/es/glossary/canvas/index.html","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/translated-content/commit/5fe4ab11259b37914fab41914e84897fea47d143","filename":"index.html"},"parents":[{"uri":"/es/docs/Glossary","title":"Glosario"},{"uri":"/es/docs/Glossary/Canvas","title":"Canvas"}],"pageTitle":"Canvas - Glosario | MDN","noIndexing":false}}